stylometry: GOAL SEEK allows you to type in a specific goal that you are looking to achieve and will give you the corisponding information that must happen to obtain that goal. For example if you are selling t-shirts and your goal is to make $300 for an organization then you can set your goal in Goal Seek to 300 and it will tell you by changing the changing cells of the t-shirts how many you must sell, factoring in costs, etc., to achieve the goal of raising $300. A DATA TABLE can then be run which allows you to see how much money you would raise if you sold less than the set amount of t-shirts to raise $300 or how much money you would raise if you sold more t-shirts than the amount to raise $300.
